1
00:00:07,833 --> 00:00:09,467
Ma'am Marj, may we talk again?

2
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:10,467
Just for a moment.

3
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:11,600
Yolly.

4
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:14,533
Can we go home for now
while waiting for a donor?

5
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:18,067
Yes, it will help her
if she is surrounded by family.

6
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,267
- Isn't that great?
- What is so great about it?

7
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:22,067
I do not need anyone's pity.

8
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:25,033
You act if you want
to get what you want.

9
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:30,600
If Greg will not remove
the house help, I will.

10
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:34,100
Is that not the hoodie
the arsonist was wearing?

11
00:00:34,267 --> 00:00:36,033
You need to know the truth now.

12
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:38,667
Ms. Yolly,
what truth do I need to know?

13
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:39,567
There she is.

14
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:40,833
Bring her at the precinct.

15
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:43,667
Sir, I am innocent! No!

16
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,533
Hello, Ms. Yolly, what happened?

17
00:01:31,567 --> 00:01:33,000
Aunt Marj!

18
00:01:37,767 --> 00:01:39,767
How is Jasmine?

19
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:42,467
By God's grace,
she is still fighting.

20
00:01:42,633 --> 00:01:46,767
She is a bit impatient now,
so she gets irritated easily.

21
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:49,800
Does that mean
I still cannot visit her?

22
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:53,733
She might just get more annoyed
with me.

23
00:01:55,633 --> 00:01:57,100
Let it be.

24
00:01:57,233 --> 00:02:01,867
She will calm down
once she gets a matching donor.

25
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,533
Her spirits will be lifted too.

26
00:02:04,667 --> 00:02:09,100
If I cannot get tested
to be her donor,

27
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:13,533
I will look for people I know
who can help.

28
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:16,733
Thank you for loving Jasmine.

29
00:02:16,867 --> 00:02:19,333
You are really like a sister
to her.

30
00:02:19,467 --> 00:02:21,000
Yes, Auntie.

31
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:24,800
That is why
I really don't want to lose her.

32
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:36,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

33
00:02:37,867 --> 00:02:38,667
Marj!

34
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:39,800
Ma'am Marj.

35
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:41,900
Ms. Yolly.

36
00:02:42,033 --> 00:02:44,033
Ma'am Marj, can we talk again?

37
00:02:44,167 --> 00:02:45,533
Just for a moment.

38
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:50,667
Okay, I still have a few minutes
before my rideshare arrives.

39
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:54,200
Yolly!

40
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:56,900
Yolly.

41
00:02:57,933 --> 00:02:59,033
Call Andres.

42
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,000
I need to go
to the dermatologist.

43
00:03:02,133 --> 00:03:05,467
I need to have this monstrosity
you gave me checked.

44
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:10,033
Why are you standing
like a statue?

45
00:03:10,167 --> 00:03:12,433
Were you petrified earlier?

46
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:13,433
For your information,

47
00:03:13,567 --> 00:03:17,233
only I am allowed
to commission statues.

48
00:03:17,367 --> 00:03:18,667
Leave.

49
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:19,700
Yes.

50
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:23,300
[NOTIFICATION CHIMES]

51
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,167
Mom, I will go ahead now.

52
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:29,467
My rideshare is already here.
Jasmine is waiting for me.

53
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,667
This is not an airport.

54
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,133
You do not need to announce
your departure.

55
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:33,433
Just go.

56
00:03:33,567 --> 00:03:43,533
[INTENSE MUSIC]

57
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,400
Yolly!

58
00:03:49,533 --> 00:03:50,500
Andres!

59
00:03:50,633 --> 00:03:57,067
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:03:57,233 --> 00:04:02,067
So, you mean we can go home for
now while waiting for a donor?

61
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:06,300
Yes, it will help her
if she is surrounded by family.

62
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:07,667
Thank you, Doctor.

63
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,433
I will leave you for now.

64
00:04:11,767 --> 00:04:14,600
Oh, my child,
did you hear that?

65
00:04:14,733 --> 00:04:16,933
You no longer have to be stuck
here in the hospital.

66
00:04:17,067 --> 00:04:18,433
Isn't that great?

67
00:04:18,567 --> 00:04:20,233
What is so great about it?

68
00:04:22,867 --> 00:04:24,900
Jas, do not be like that.

69
00:04:25,033 --> 00:04:27,133
I go home and then what?

70
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:29,333
People at home will just pretend
to be nice to me

71
00:04:29,467 --> 00:04:30,567
because I am sick.

72
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,600
My child, that
is not true.

73
00:04:33,733 --> 00:04:34,700
You are only saying that, Mom,

74
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:37,433
because you do not feel
what I am feeling.

75
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:39,833
Jas, do not talk
to your mother like that.

76
00:04:39,967 --> 00:04:41,400
Okay, dear.

77
00:04:42,433 --> 00:04:45,400
Jasmine, did we not talk
about this already?

78
00:04:45,533 --> 00:04:48,633
Please, do not act like that.

79
00:04:48,767 --> 00:04:51,167
I just do not need anyone
seeing me like this.

80
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,867
I do not need anyone's pity.

81
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,533
What I need is a donor
so I can get better.

82
00:04:56,667 --> 00:04:59,500
I still want to experience
so many things.

83
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:02,100
There are so many places
I want to go to.

84
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:04,300
I want to eat
delicious food again.

85
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:06,133
And do all those things
with my friends

86
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:09,300
but I cannot because
of this cancer.

87
00:05:09,433 --> 00:05:11,667
- Jasmine.
- Now I am starting to lose

88
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,033
all my hair!

89
00:05:13,167 --> 00:05:15,700
So now I am sick and ugly.

90
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:19,033
I hate this! I hate everything
that is wrong with me!

91
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:29,133
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

92
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:49,200
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

93
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:51,400
Mrs. Torrecampo?

94
00:05:52,533 --> 00:05:53,733
Aldrin Castelo.

95
00:05:53,867 --> 00:05:55,033
I work for your husband.

96
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:00,833
Hello, Mr. Castelo.
I know who you are.

97
00:06:00,967 --> 00:06:02,867
- You sold the Menagerie units.
- Yes.

98
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,700
- Good job.
- Thank you.

99
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:07,267
It is nice to finally meet you
again, Mrs. Torrecampo.

100
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,200
But if you do not mind
me asking,

101
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,333
why are you drinking here alone?

102
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:17,600
Well, when your husband
upsets you for the nth time

103
00:06:17,733 --> 00:06:21,400
and over an elderly maid
he sides with.

104
00:06:21,533 --> 00:06:25,633
Not even liquor can numb
the pain, but I still try.

105
00:06:25,767 --> 00:06:27,700
Well, it looks like you are
going through something heavy.

106
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:29,000
How unfortunate.

107
00:06:31,433 --> 00:06:32,633
Please, sit down.

108
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:38,300
Oh dear, maybe...

109
00:06:38,433 --> 00:06:40,867
Greg should have been
a magician.

110
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,600
Maybe he could make me disappear
or cut me in half

111
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:45,800
because that would be less
painful.

112
00:06:47,267 --> 00:06:49,200
Well, to be honest,
Mrs. Torrecampo,

113
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:50,467
I did not expect

114
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:53,133
your relationship with Sir Greg
to be like that.

115
00:06:53,267 --> 00:06:54,867
If you are familiar
with the saying,

116
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,967
behind every great man
is an even greater woman.

117
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:02,367
And that is what comes
to mind when I see you both.

118
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:07,433
Cheers!

119
00:07:07,567 --> 00:07:09,867
And I still think that is true.

120
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,233
Maybe you are just too kind,

121
00:07:12,367 --> 00:07:14,133
and Sir Greg takes advantage
of that.

122
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:15,567
[CHUCKLES]

123
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:20,533
He told me I am the one
abusing his kindness.

124
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:24,633
Well, unsolicited advice.

125
00:07:24,767 --> 00:07:26,233
Do not let him get to you.

126
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:30,733
Do not let him destroy
your self-esteem.

127
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:35,967
I believe you deserve better.

128
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,967
I think that is quite bold
of you to suggest

129
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,500
for someone you just met.

130
00:07:41,633 --> 00:07:43,300
That is because I think
you need it.

131
00:07:45,467 --> 00:07:48,200
Be like the woman
my father always told me about.

132
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:52,133
And why would I want
to be like that woman?

133
00:07:53,467 --> 00:07:56,200
Because she was
the greatest love of his life.

134
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:00,467
A strong woman...

135
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,567
who would never let herself
be outplayed.

136
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:05,467
Someone who knows herself well.

137
00:08:07,633 --> 00:08:10,200
Someone who will not let anyone
dim her shine.

138
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:15,967
So, do not let your husband
dim your shine, Mrs. Torrecampo.

139
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:20,433
I believe you can still be that
great woman behind your husband.

140
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:29,900
- Thank you, Aldrin.
- Cheers!

141
00:08:30,033 --> 00:08:31,367
I will remember that.

142
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:41,467
[INTENSE MUSIC]

143
00:08:56,267 --> 00:08:57,900
Ash.

144
00:08:58,033 --> 00:08:59,200
Ash.

145
00:09:01,367 --> 00:09:02,933
Did I not tell you to stay
away from me for now?

146
00:09:04,267 --> 00:09:06,233
What do I need to do
for you to talk to me again?

147
00:09:06,367 --> 00:09:08,500
For you to stop being so upset
with me?

148
00:09:08,633 --> 00:09:11,000
There is only one thing
I want right now.

149
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:12,800
For Jasmine to get better.

150
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:15,400
That is what you want too,
right?

151
00:09:15,533 --> 00:09:18,600
Well, I would be less upset
if you just liked her instead.

152
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:19,800
What?

153
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:22,067
Do you know how ridiculous
you sound right now?

154
00:09:22,933 --> 00:09:23,833
Ridiculous?

155
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:26,900
Is she not
important to you?

156
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:31,233
So, you know what, court her
instead and forget about me.

157
00:09:31,367 --> 00:09:32,767
I cannot do that.

158
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:34,867
I am not going to do that.

159
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,067
It would be unfair to her.

160
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,233
Especially if she finds out
the truth,

161
00:09:39,367 --> 00:09:40,800
she will be even more hurt.

162
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:42,233
Then she will hate both of us.

163
00:09:42,367 --> 00:09:43,467
Do you want that?

164
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,367
Of course not, Xander.

165
00:09:46,733 --> 00:09:48,433
But I want to make it up to her.

166
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:50,700
Make it up to her?

167
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:51,833
Why?

168
00:09:53,767 --> 00:09:55,733
Because of what my mother did
with her father.

169
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:58,867
But that is not your fault, Ash.

170
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,033
Why do you need to be the one

171
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,767
to make it up to Jasmine and her
mom?

172
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:06,600
Why are you punishing
yourself, Ash?

173
00:10:06,733 --> 00:10:09,167
Because I want to do
something for Jasmine.

174
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,933
To help her get better.

175
00:10:12,067 --> 00:10:16,167
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

176
00:10:16,300 --> 00:10:19,500
Because I no longer know what
else I can do aside from...

177
00:10:19,633 --> 00:10:21,433
Aside from pushing me toward
her?

178
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:27,533
And have you not thought
about how unfair that plan is?

179
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:31,867
Xander, there is no fairness in
Jasmine's condition right now.

180
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,267
Do you understand?

181
00:10:34,667 --> 00:10:36,133
I know that.

182
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,000
But Ash,

183
00:10:40,167 --> 00:10:42,300
that is not a reason...

184
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:44,033
to be miserable.

185
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:49,700
Yes, we do not want to lose
Jasmine.

186
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,133
But that should not stop you

187
00:10:52,267 --> 00:10:54,067
from living the life
you deserve, Ash.

188
00:10:54,200 --> 00:11:04,167
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

189
00:11:08,567 --> 00:11:10,333
Mrs. Torrecampo.

190
00:11:10,467 --> 00:11:11,767
Heading home so soon?

191
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,267
[CHUCKLES]

192
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,167
I just had a drink.

193
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:17,000
I was just passing time
after work.

194
00:11:18,333 --> 00:11:20,200
I did not want
to go home early.

195
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:22,767
I did not want to
see my spouse's face.

196
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:24,567
I get that.

197
00:11:26,733 --> 00:11:30,000
And thank you for the
unexpected company last night.

198
00:11:30,133 --> 00:11:32,400
I guess we were both in the
right place at the right time.

199
00:11:32,533 --> 00:11:34,900
[CHUCKLES]

200
00:11:35,033 --> 00:11:37,833
Oh, have you resolved
the problem at home?

201
00:11:37,967 --> 00:11:39,767
How can I resolve it

202
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:41,967
when my husband
will not even listen to me?

203
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:44,200
Well,

204
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:45,767
if your spouse refuses to listen
to you

205
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:48,600
and is always undermining
and ignoring you,

206
00:11:48,733 --> 00:11:51,633
and constantly humiliates you
in front of others, as you said,

207
00:11:52,633 --> 00:11:55,533
then I think it is time
for you to step up.

208
00:11:55,667 --> 00:11:58,567
You take action
to get what you want.

209
00:12:00,967 --> 00:12:03,500
You know, you are right about
that.

210
00:12:03,633 --> 00:12:09,500
If Greg will not remove
the house help, I will.

211
00:12:09,633 --> 00:12:12,967
After all, I am still the queen
of his kingdom.

212
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:16,067
These days, you can even
be king if you want to.

213
00:12:16,233 --> 00:12:17,267
Oh, I like that.

214
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,333
[LAUGHS]

215
00:12:18,467 --> 00:12:21,700
Thank you for humoring this old
woman, Aldrin.

216
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:28,367
Is there a problem,
Mrs. Torrecampo?

217
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:31,067
Is there dirt on my face?

218
00:12:32,233 --> 00:12:33,400
No, none.

219
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:38,667
You look like someone
I knew from my past.

220
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,700
Who was it?

221
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:44,900
[CHUCKLES]

222
00:12:45,033 --> 00:12:48,133
Nothing.
I must have been mistaken.

223
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:50,967
Anyway, I will go ahead.
My car is over there.

224
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,200
Oh, do you want me to take you?
I can give you a ride.

225
00:12:52,333 --> 00:12:53,167
No, no, no! It is okay.

226
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:53,867
- I can manage.
- Are you sure?

227
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,767
Yes, yes. I am sure.

228
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,567
- I will see you tomorrow?
- Yes.

229
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:58,700
- I will see you.
- Bye, Aldrin!

230
00:12:58,833 --> 00:13:00,200
- Good night!
- Good night!

231
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:10,300
[INTENSE MUSIC]

232
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:15,867
Mom, I am sorry.

233
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,700
It's been a while since I last
visited you ang Jobert.

234
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:21,233
Oh, my child.

235
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:24,767
Don't worry about us, my child.

236
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:29,800
I understand that Jasmine
really needs you with her.

237
00:13:29,933 --> 00:13:31,600
She needs you more, my child.

238
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:33,767
So please,
make sure you eat, okay?

239
00:13:33,900 --> 00:13:35,933
You must not get weak.

240
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:39,133
Have they still not found
a donor?

241
00:13:41,233 --> 00:13:42,567
Still none, Mom.

242
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:46,533
We haven't stopped looking, but
still there's no one.

243
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:52,433
Days have passed,
and my child is losing hope.

244
00:13:52,567 --> 00:13:55,967
Even I am breaking from fear
and worry.

245
00:13:56,133 --> 00:13:59,000
Of course, I am trying
to stay strong, but...

246
00:14:00,233 --> 00:14:01,867
Oh my, my child.

247
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,167
You know,

248
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,367
that is how it is sometimes.

249
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:08,333
Sometimes, we just have
to leave everything to God.

250
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:14,400
Marj,
do you remember Father Vera?

251
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:16,933
- Your cousin who is a priest?
- Yes.

252
00:14:17,067 --> 00:14:20,867
I can call him
so he can pray over Jasmine.

253
00:14:21,767 --> 00:14:23,300
And...

254
00:14:23,433 --> 00:14:25,300
also pray over you and Paolo.

255
00:14:25,433 --> 00:14:29,533
To give you strength and hope.

256
00:14:32,167 --> 00:14:34,600
Thank you, Mom.

257
00:14:34,733 --> 00:14:39,367
[PHONE RINGING]

258
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:41,200
Hello, Ms. Yolly?

259
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:44,700
Ma'am Marj, I am going
to the hospital tomorrow.

260
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:48,367
I just wanted to ask
if you want me to cook anything.

261
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:49,867
I can bring it there.

262
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,433
Nothing, Ms. Yolly.
Thank you very much.

263
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:55,267
Are you okay? Are you sick?

264
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,600
I am fine.

265
00:14:56,733 --> 00:14:58,700
I wanted to...

266
00:14:58,833 --> 00:15:04,500
aside from visiting Jasmine,
I also wanted to talk to you.

267
00:15:04,667 --> 00:15:06,700
Oh yes, you wanted
to tell me something.

268
00:15:06,833 --> 00:15:07,900
What is it?

269
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:10,367
Why can you not say it
over the phone?

270
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:12,433
Oh, Marj, I cannot!

271
00:15:12,567 --> 00:15:14,000
It is important.

272
00:15:14,133 --> 00:15:16,200
We need to talk face to face.

273
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:19,100
All right. We are just here
at the hospital.

274
00:15:19,233 --> 00:15:21,300
But we are going home tomorrow.

275
00:15:21,433 --> 00:15:24,733
Just wait for me, okay?
Thank you.

276
00:15:24,867 --> 00:15:26,833
Yes, Ms. Yolly. Thank you.

277
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:36,900
[TENSE MUSIC]

278
00:15:37,933 --> 00:15:41,133
There have been reactions
to my post...

279
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:43,300
to my post looking for a donor,

280
00:15:43,433 --> 00:15:46,067
but no one has messaged me yet
who is willing to get tested.

281
00:15:47,033 --> 00:15:49,133
I already spoke
with the donor registry.

282
00:15:50,367 --> 00:15:52,433
They still cannot find anyone

283
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:56,433
compatible with Jasmine's HLA
type.

284
00:15:56,567 --> 00:16:01,733
They told me the probability
is one in 20,000

285
00:16:01,867 --> 00:16:04,733
that Jasmine will find a match
outside our blood relatives.

286
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:09,867
I do not know what else to do.

287
00:16:12,133 --> 00:16:14,867
I am completely
drained, Paolo.

288
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,067
Just like our options.

289
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:22,167
It hurts so much that we cannot
do anything for our own child.

290
00:16:24,133 --> 00:16:26,100
I have been crying nonstop.

291
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:33,667
I know my tears
will not help Jasmine, but...

292
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:35,800
I feel completely useless.

293
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,000
Do not say that, Marj.

294
00:16:39,133 --> 00:16:41,100
You are doing your best.

295
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:44,067
Even if you ask Jasmine,

296
00:16:44,233 --> 00:16:47,200
she would choose
no other mother but you.

297
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:57,300
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

298
00:17:24,067 --> 00:17:26,433
[TENSE MUSIC]

299
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:28,000
I am on my way.

300
00:17:28,133 --> 00:17:30,800
I will also help you with
Jasmine's discharge.

301
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:40,367
[TENSE MUSIC]

302
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:43,033
So, you are saying
the fire was intentional?

303
00:17:43,167 --> 00:17:44,867
Based on the investigation,

304
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:48,500
the fire started in different
areas inside the house.

305
00:17:48,667 --> 00:17:51,167
That is why we suspect arson.

306
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:54,067
It is possible
that this was an inside job.

307
00:17:55,367 --> 00:17:57,033
So, you will conduct
an investigation

308
00:17:57,167 --> 00:17:59,000
to determine who the possible
arsonist is?

309
00:17:59,133 --> 00:18:07,167
[INTENSE MUSIC]

310
00:18:07,300 --> 00:18:09,333
Yolly, where are you going?

311
00:18:09,467 --> 00:18:10,600
To the hospital.

312
00:18:10,733 --> 00:18:14,267
I am just bringing something
for Ma'am Marj and Jasmine.

313
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,400
No, that is not allowed.
You need to stay here.

314
00:18:16,533 --> 00:18:18,900
You were part of the household
when the fire happened.

315
00:18:19,033 --> 00:18:20,900
You need to be investigated.

316
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:23,367
Unless you are scared because
you are hiding something?

317
00:18:23,533 --> 00:18:26,167
Oh no, I am not.
I have nothing to hide.

318
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:27,500
Then there is no problem.

319
00:18:27,633 --> 00:18:28,867
Then stay.

320
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,900
[INTENSE MUSIC]

321
00:18:31,033 --> 00:18:32,400
Like a good dog.

322
00:18:33,567 --> 00:18:43,533
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

323
00:18:46,267 --> 00:18:50,267
<i>We're sorry, the number you have
reached is not in service.</i>

324
00:18:52,233 --> 00:18:54,067
What are you doing here?

325
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:57,700
Should we not be preparing
for Jasmine's release?

326
00:18:57,867 --> 00:18:59,867
I am waiting
for Ms. Yolly.

327
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:03,133
She said she has something
important to tell me.

328
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:05,633
She should have been here
by now, but she is not.

329
00:19:05,767 --> 00:19:09,200
That is why I am calling, in
case something happened to her.

330
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:11,767
Why do you need
to meet here?

331
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,900
Why not just at the house?
We are going home anyway.

332
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:15,767
Jasmine is waiting for us.

333
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:18,833
Just message her
that we are on our way home.

334
00:19:18,967 --> 00:19:20,867
And Mom is also looking for us.

335
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,600
Something about the fire.

336
00:19:24,767 --> 00:19:25,767
Okay.

337
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:40,267
[INTENSE MUSIC]

338
00:19:52,867 --> 00:19:54,900
What are you doing there?

339
00:19:55,033 --> 00:20:05,000
[INTENSE MUSIC]

340
00:20:09,267 --> 00:20:12,533
Ma'am. I was just checking the
hose in case I left it open.

341
00:20:12,667 --> 00:20:13,700
That is enough.

342
00:20:13,833 --> 00:20:15,567
Go inside and the police
will check your belongings.

343
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:17,533
- Yes.
- Hurry up.

344
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:24,100
[INTENSE MUSIC]

345
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:25,900
Come here.

346
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:28,867
Search everything.

347
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:33,533
Check if there is a voodoo doll
there or some shady potion

348
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:37,433
because I have a
witch for a house help.

349
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:47,567
[INTENSE MUSIC]

350
00:20:55,267 --> 00:20:56,867
Please be careful over there.

351
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,333
I have some
fragile perfume bottles there.

352
00:20:59,467 --> 00:21:09,433
[INTENSE MUSIC]

353
00:21:33,533 --> 00:21:38,533
Is that not the hoodie Marj said
the arsonist was wearing?

354
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,833
Whose cabinet is that?

355
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,333
Ma'am, that belongs to Ms.
Yolly.

356
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,967
Chase her. She has not gone far!

357
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:49,567
Hurry!

358
00:21:51,933 --> 00:21:52,933
Come on!

359
00:21:57,067 --> 00:21:58,100
Slowly, my child.

360
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:01,867
Mom, I do not really need
a wheelchair. I can walk.

361
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:04,200
My child, you are still weak.

362
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:06,700
Okay? It is fine to use
a wheelchair.

363
00:22:06,833 --> 00:22:08,667
As long as you are
okay, all right?

364
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:15,967
[PHONE RINGING]

365
00:22:16,133 --> 00:22:17,400
Hello, Ms. Yolly?

366
00:22:17,533 --> 00:22:18,967
Oh, we are heading home there
as well.

367
00:22:19,100 --> 00:22:20,200
Let us just talk there.

368
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:22,600
Ma'am Marj,
you need to know the truth.

369
00:22:24,033 --> 00:22:25,000
What truth?

370
00:22:25,967 --> 00:22:28,133
Ms. Yolly,
what truth do I need to know?

371
00:22:28,267 --> 00:22:31,833
[INTENSE MUSIC]

372
00:22:31,967 --> 00:22:33,000
There she is.

373
00:22:33,133 --> 00:22:35,967
[INTENSE MUSIC]

374
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:37,433
Hello?

375
00:22:37,567 --> 00:22:40,567
Ms. Yolly,
what is happening to you?

376
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:42,433
Ms. Yolly?

377
00:22:42,567 --> 00:22:43,900
Hey! Stop!

378
00:22:47,333 --> 00:22:49,233
Hello, Ms. Yolly? What happened?

379
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:52,133
[CALL DISCONNECTED]

380
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:56,633
[INTENSE MUSIC]

381
00:22:56,767 --> 00:22:57,833
*

382
00:22:57,967 --> 00:23:00,600
[INTENSE MUSIC]

383
00:23:00,733 --> 00:23:01,800
What is going on?

384
00:23:01,933 --> 00:23:08,200
[INTENSE MUSIC]

385
00:23:08,333 --> 00:23:10,267
There!

386
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,400
We just found this black hoodie

387
00:23:12,533 --> 00:23:15,667
in the cabinet
of your favorite house servant.

388
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:19,300
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

389
00:23:19,433 --> 00:23:21,333
That is not mine, Sir Greg.

390
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:22,733
Please believe me.

391
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:26,200
We will have her belongings
checked by forensics.

392
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:33,033
Did you intentionally burn
my house?

393
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:36,867
My inheritance passed down
from my ancestors!

394
00:23:38,567 --> 00:23:39,533
Why?

395
00:23:40,733 --> 00:23:42,400
Because I fired you?

396
00:23:42,533 --> 00:23:44,067
No.

397
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:46,467
Sir, I am innocent.

398
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,533
Please, believe me.

399
00:23:48,667 --> 00:23:51,600
Someone else placed that
in my cabinet, Sir.

400
00:23:51,733 --> 00:23:53,833
I am certain.

401
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:56,367
Take her to the precinct.

402
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:57,700
Sir Greg!

403
00:23:57,833 --> 00:24:01,367
You are under arrest for arson
of Torrecampo family property.

404
00:24:01,500 --> 00:24:04,167
Based on the evidence
found among your belongings.

405
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:06,567
You have the right
to remain silent.

406
00:24:06,700 --> 00:24:09,233
Anything you say
may be used in court.

407
00:24:09,367 --> 00:24:11,400
If you cannot afford a lawyer,

408
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:12,967
the government
will provide one for you.

409
00:24:13,100 --> 00:24:14,533
Do you understand this?

410
00:24:14,667 --> 00:24:17,767
[INTENSE MUSIC]

411
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:20,767
Please believe me, Sir!

412
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:23,133
Please believe me!

413
00:24:31,567 --> 00:24:34,533
Dad already told us about what
happened to Ms. Yolly.

414
00:24:34,667 --> 00:24:38,167
I cannot understand if Ms. Yolly
is really the arsonist.

415
00:24:38,300 --> 00:24:41,000
Why would she leave the hoodie
where it could be easily found?

416
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:45,200
That is exactly
what I thought too, Ma'am.

417
00:24:45,333 --> 00:24:46,633
That is why I believe
what she said,

418
00:24:46,767 --> 00:24:49,500
that she was just set up,
is true.

419
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:53,933
But she is not really
a criminal by nature, right?

420
00:24:54,067 --> 00:24:56,867
So maybe she panicked
or got confused

421
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,567
and failed to hide her things
properly?

422
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:02,500
Because why would
it be there, right?

423
00:25:02,667 --> 00:25:05,967
I do not know, but it would be
shocking if it is true.

424
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:10,600
As sad as it is to think
about, I really feel it is true.

425
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:14,700
Ms. Yolly called me earlier.

426
00:25:16,133 --> 00:25:18,500
She said there is something
I need to know.

427
00:25:18,633 --> 00:25:21,267
Maybe she is about to confess
that she burned the house?

428
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:31,367
[INTENSE MUSIC]

429
00:25:32,833 --> 00:25:33,833
Lord...

430
00:25:33,967 --> 00:25:37,067
please cleanse the air
inside this house

431
00:25:37,233 --> 00:25:40,500
and shake off
any negative energy

432
00:25:40,633 --> 00:25:44,233
that keeps disturbing
and dividing our family.

433
00:25:44,367 --> 00:25:47,500
Because how can we ask
for a miracle for Jasmine

434
00:25:47,633 --> 00:25:49,333
if the foundation of our home

435
00:25:49,467 --> 00:25:52,300
is built on pride
and a lack of respect?

436
00:25:52,433 --> 00:25:55,733
Hello, Mr. Torrecampo!
This is Police Major Santos.

437
00:25:55,867 --> 00:25:59,700
I am calling to inform you that
your housekeeper has escaped!

438
00:25:59,833 --> 00:26:01,600
What?

439
00:26:01,733 --> 00:26:03,300
You are completely useless!

440
00:26:03,433 --> 00:26:07,233
Order our guards to secure
the perimeter of the house.

441
00:26:07,367 --> 00:26:10,200
Yolly escaped,
she will surely retaliate!

442
00:26:11,367 --> 00:26:12,433
Ms. Yolly?

443
00:26:12,567 --> 00:26:13,600
What are you doing here?

444
00:26:13,733 --> 00:26:17,100
I want to help you find
a donor for Jasmine.

445
00:26:17,233 --> 00:26:21,233
I want you to know a hidden
secret of the Torrecampo family.

446
00:26:21,367 --> 00:26:23,467
What is this? A paternity test?

447
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:25,833
Thea. Thea and Paolo?

448
00:26:25,967 --> 00:26:28,633
Ashley is their child,
Ma'am Marj.
